# Diff: ~/.claude/settings.json (DRAFT, do not auto-apply)

Source-of-truth read on 2026-04-24 from `C:/Users/mattm/.claude/settings.json`.

## Rationale (one line each)

- **`skipDangerousModePermissionPrompt: true` -> removed.** Audit Theme F + under-weighted risk #4: combined with `bypassPermissions`, there is no boundary at all. A single prompt-injected document can rewrite the filesystem.
- **`defaultMode: bypassPermissions` -> kept for now**, but the prompt skip is removed so dangerous patterns at least surface. Downgrading the default mode is a separate, larger decision (see `05-application-instructions.md`).
- **Allowlist trimmed of one-shot, project-specific entries.** The two giant `git commit -m "$(cat <<EOF ... EOF)"` strings and the matching `gh pr create --title "..."` strings are pinned to specific RSMF Phase 2 / Phase 5 commit bodies. They will never re-match a future commit (the body changes every time). They were captured one-shot and forgotten — exactly the dead weight Theme D flags.
- **`Bash(.venv/Scripts/python -m pytest tests/unit/ -v --tb=short)` -> kept as `Bash(.venv/Scripts/python:*)` already covers it.** Removed the redundant entry.
- **`Bash(git -C D:/github/RSMFConverter status)` and the matching `git log --oneline -5` -> removed.** Single-repo pinned forms; the broader `Bash(git log:*)` (in `settings.local.json`) handles this category.
- **Kept:** all generic `git`, `pip`, `python`, `poetry`, `gh pr create:*`-style globs that match a real recurring need.

